values:
&ldquo;Though dreams can be deceiving, like faces are to hearts, they serve for sweet relieving, when fantasy and reality lie too far apart.&rdquo;

Fresh back from vacation! Woot! Spent almost a week in Sutton, my whole bottom half is sore from constant 4wheelin adventures, but cannot WAIT to go back. This weekend the whole fam is heading for Homer for some commercial fishing. Course, I'll be holding down the camp with my good ole alaskan husky (who apparently LOVES camping, lol, didn't have her on a leash at all! So proud, my baby is growing up *sniffle*) Poor me you say? NOPE. Eff boats, don't much like boats (I won't mention the fact that I can't swim) because they float on water, and I hate water. Give me some ice over water&nbsp;any day.

Camping with no one but my hubby and my dog was just awesome. Nothing better than SILENCE (or just the sound of the 4wheel engine) We rode and Lilly chased, you want to see one happy husky, get her to run as fast as she can. lol. It was priceless, tongue hanging out, big shit eating grin, ears back, just beaming.
We camped right against the bottom of a mountain (a very steep one) and there was a huge rock about 100 feet up. Lilly climbed up to the rock and would lay there for hours 'watching over the camp'. Lol, I have the best dog ever. She also&nbsp;buried a bone, which I've never seen her do before, poor city-bound dog.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Guess I should bite back into my unfinished meme...

&nbsp;day 5 - discuss your feelings on the word &ldquo;love&rdquo; and the way it&rsquo;s used in today
I think love has many forms. For example I love sushi, I love my fam, I love my hubby, I love to read, I love sports... all in different ways. I use the word love to describe the things/people I hold close to my heart or would hate to live without. If I was suddenly paralyzed I would be&nbsp;devastated. Not because I couldn't walk or do other things, but because I couldn't skate, or slide into home, or dive for a frisbee. I def would pick up wheelchair hockey and anything else I could though... I guess I would be ok now that I think about it, I could feel the wind in my hair from the back of a rig (I hate running anyways) and play frisbee golf (I might not have a killer drive anymore but I could make it work.) ........well geez I've got way off track here.
The way the word is used today, sure people through it around who prob shouldn't, but that's just because they don't understand it. LOVE on those people because they need it the most.&nbsp;

Coming up on a crossroads is frightening.&nbsp;
We will be leaving Alaska in a few months (after one last amazing summer where the sun never sets) to follow his music. He's an amazing artist, will break your heart with his guitar, make you melt with his voice, and baffle you with his drumsticks. I never really thought of a drum set as a stand-alone instrument like a piano, but *dear Lord* he can make those skins purrr. I could listen to him play his bluesy drums for hours in perfect contentment, he has the&nbsp;ability&nbsp;to play directly out of his soul. It's amazing.&nbsp;
It'd be selfish of me to keep him all to myself. So we are moving to California or Texas to start and are going to follow the blues crowd. I would think that I'm bias (since I'm married to him after all) but wherever he plays.... he captivates people, moves some to tears. He has something special, this is what he was made for.

So HELLO adventure says the square!&nbsp;
